1. DEFINITIONS

“BBS” — the Big Begins Small digital ecosystem, including its architecture, concepts, structures, documentation, core models, platform modules, integrity systems, AI principles, and any related materials.

“Author” — Pavlo Martseniuk, creator and rights holder.

“You” — any individual, institution, company, or government using BBS.

“Derivative Work” — any modification, extension, adaptation, or partial reuse of BBS or its components.

2. PERMITTED USE

You are allowed to:

Use BBS for non-commercial, academic, research, educational, civic, humanitarian, and transparency-oriented purposes.

Study, analyze, and understand the system.

Create derivative works only if they remain open and published under this same license.

Share BBS publicly, with attribution to the Author.

Integrate BBS concepts into public-benefit systems, provided ethical rules are upheld.

3. PROHIBITED USE (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

Any violation of this section automatically terminates all rights granted by this license.

It is strictly prohibited to use BBS for:

3.1. Corruption

financial fraud

illegal enrichment

bribery

manipulation of public funds

falsification of records

interference with audit or transparency systems

3.2. Political Manipulation

influencing elections

propagandistic manipulation

censorship

psychological or mass-behavioural manipulation

misuse by political parties or shadow structures

3.3. Harm to Humans

surveillance without consent

social scoring

exploitation or discrimination

abuse of vulnerable populations

weaponization of data

3.4. Commercial Exploitation Without Permission

You may not:

sell BBS or its derivatives

package BBS into commercial products

offer BBS-based paid services

use BBS for corporate profit

unless explicit written permission from the Author is obtained.

3.5. Patenting & Ownership Claims

You may not:

patent any part of BBS

register its concepts as intellectual property

claim authorship or joint ownership

restrict others from using BBS

Any attempt to patent or privatize BBS is void and legally challengeable.

4. ETHICAL REQUIREMENTS (MANDATORY)

All users of BBS must adhere to:

4.1. Truth Alignment

All implementations must preserve accuracy, transparency, and evidence-based logic.

4.2. Human Dignity First

No action may harm or diminish human rights.

4.3. Transparency

All modifications and derivative works must be:

open

published

accessible to the public

logged transparently

4.4. Responsibility

You accept full responsibility for your use of BBS.

5. DERIVATIVE WORKS

Any derivative work:

must be published under BBS-PL, without exceptions

must include full attribution to the Author

must not hide or obscure internal logic

must remain transparent and open

must not weaken ethical protections

Private or closed-source derivatives are prohibited.

6. WARRANTY DISCLAIMER

BBS is provided “as is”, with no warranties of any kind.

The Author shall not be liable for:

damages

data loss

misuse by third parties

legal consequences of improper use

7. TERMINATION

Your rights under this license terminate immediately if you:

violate any ethical rule

engage in corruption

attempt political misuse

exploit BBS commercially without permission

attempt to patent or privatize BBS

breach transparency requirements

Termination is automatic and irreversible.

8. NO WAIVER OF RIGHTS

The Author retains all rights not explicitly granted here.

9. JURISDICTION

This license is valid internationally.
Legal disputes may be brought in any competent court chosen by the Author.

10. PURPOSE OF BBS-PL

To ensure that BBS remains:

ethical

